The PAMB shall be the policy-making body of the MKNP. It shall be composed of:

The Regional Executive Directors (RED) of DENR Regions VI and VII, with the RED of Region VI as PAMB chair;

The Governors of Negros Occidental and Negros Oriental, or their respective duly authorized regular representatives;

The mayors of municipalities and cities with territory within the MKNP, or their respective duly authorized regular representatives;

All barangay captains of barangays with territory within MKNP, or their respective duly authorized regular representatives;

Three (3) representatives from NGOs based in Negros Occidental which are accredited with the DENR and the LGU and with tangible projects at the time of their membership in the PAMB;

A PO representative chosen from among themselves for each municipality and city with territory within the MKNP:

Provided,

That the POs are accredited with the DENR and the LGU and with tangible projects at the time of their membership in the PAMB;

The Provincial Planning and Development Officers (PPDO) of Negros Occidental and Negros Oriental;

The Provincial Planning and Development Officers (PPDO) of Negros Occidental and Negros Oriental;

An ICC/IP representative for each tribal community within the MKNP; and

A duly authorized representative with environmental expertise of the Philippine National Oil Company Energy Development Corporation (PNOC EDC).

There shall be an Executive Committee (Execom) within the PAMB to whom the PAMB may delegate some of its powers and functions. It shall be composed of:

The RED of DENR Region VI as chairman;

The Governors of Negros Occidental and Negros Oriental, or their respective duly authorized, regular representatives;

Two (2) mayor representatives, to be chosen from among themselves, or their respective duly authorized, regular representatives;

Two (2) barangay captain representatives, one each from Negros Occidental and Negros Oriental, to be chosen from among themselves; or their respective duly authorized, regular representatives;

One (1) from the NGO representatives;

One (1) from the PO representatives;

One (1) from the ICC/IP representatives; and

One (1) from the PNOCEDC.

